{"title_page": "Old Town Hall, Szombierki", "text_new": "{{Infobox building\n| name                = Stary Ratusz w Szombierkach\n| image               = File:Bytom Szombierki town hall.jpg\n| image_size          = 250\n| caption             = The old town hall in 2018.\n| building_type       = Town hall\n| architectural_style = \n| location            = Bytom, Poland\n| map_type            = Silesian_Voivodeship\n| coordinates         = {{coord|50|20|14.3|N|18|53|34.87|E|display=inline,title}}\n| groundbreaking_date = \n| start_date          = \n| completion_date     = 1913\n| opened_date         = \n| inauguration_date   = \n| renovation_date     = 2009\n| demolition_date     = \n| destruction_date    = \n| architect           =\n}}\nThe '''old town hall, Szombierki''' ([[Polish Language|Polish]]: ''Stary Ratusz w Szombierkach'', [[German Language|German]]: ''Schomberg Rathaus'') is a townhall building in [[Szombierki]] (a district of the city of [[Bytom]]), Poland. It used to be as the seat of the local government of the [[Schomberg (Municipality)|Schomberg Municipality]] (Until 1945), and later the [[Gmina Chruszcz\u00f3w]] (1945-1951).<ref name=\"auto\">Przemys\u0142aw Nadolski: Szombierki. In: Dzielnice Bytomia na starych fotografiach, poczt\u00f3wkach i planach. Bytom: Towarzystwo Mi\u0142o\u015bnik\u00f3w Bytomia, 1998, s. 42\u201343. {{ISBN|83-908018-1-7}}</ref>\n\n==Memorial of the Casualties of the First World War==\nIn front of the town hall used to be a memorial of the casualties  of the [[WWI|First World War]] from Szombierki (then Schomberg), a Russian mortar captured in [[Kaunas]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> The memorial was destroyed in 1945 and the pedestal during renovations in 2009.<ref>Iwona Sobczyk: Szombierki odzyskaj\u0105 ratusz, plac si\u0119 zazieleni. Gazeta Wyborcza Katowice, 2009-08-30.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n\n[[Category:Bytom]]\n[[Category:Szombierki]]\n[[Category:City and town halls in Poland]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Bytom]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1913]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox building\n| name                = Stary Ratusz w Szombierkach\n| image               = File:Bytom Szombierki town hall.jpg\n| image_size          = 250\n| caption             = The old town hall in 2018.\n| building_type       = Town hall\n| architectural_style = \n| location            = Bytom, Poland\n| map_type            = Silesian_Voivodeship\n| coordinates         = {{coord|50|20|14.3|N|18|53|34.87|E|display=inline,title}}\n| groundbreaking_date = \n| start_date          = \n| completion_date     = 1913\n| opened_date         = \n| inauguration_date   = \n| renovation_date     = 2009\n| demolition_date     = \n| destruction_date    = \n| architect           =\n}}\nThe '''old town hall, Szombierki''' ([[Polish Language|Polish]]: ''Stary Ratusz w Szombierkach'', [[German Language|German]]: ''Schomberg Rathaus'') is a townhall building in [[Szombierki]] (a district of the city of [[Bytom]]), Poland. It used to be as the seat of the local government of the [[Schomberg (Municipality)|Schomberg Municipality]] (Until 1945), and later the [[Gmina Chruszcz\u00f3w]] (1945-1951).<ref name=\"auto\">Przemys\u0142aw Nadolski: Szombierki. In: Dzielnice Bytomia na starych fotografiach, poczt\u00f3wkach i planach. Bytom: Towarzystwo Mi\u0142o\u015bnik\u00f3w Bytomia, 1998, s. 42\u201343. {{ISBN|83-908018-1-7}}</ref>\n\n==Memorial of the Casualties of the First World War==\nIn front of the town hall used to be a memorial of the casualties  of the [[WWI|First World War]] from Szombierki (then Schomberg), a Russian mortar captured in [[Kaunas]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> The memorial was destroyed in 1945 and the pedestal during renovations in 2009.<ref>Iwona Sobczyk: Szombierki odzyskaj\u0105 ratusz, plac si\u0119 zazieleni. Gazeta Wyborcza Katowice, 2009-08-30.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n\n[[Category:Bytom]]\n[[Category:Szombierki]]\n[[Category:City and town halls in Poland]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1913]]\n", "name_user": "He\u0142mPolski", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Town_Hall,_Szombierki"}
